The paper deals with the use of Neuroevolution and Gated Recurrent Units to evolve control policies for simulated robots navigating indoor mazes. This involves the use of artificial intelligence and machine learning techniques, which are typically covered under the cs.AI sub-category. The paper also deals with robotics and control systems, which are covered under the cs.RO sub-category. The use of neural networks and recurrent units falls under the cs.NE sub-category. The paper also deals with learning and optimization, which are covered under the cs.LG sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with systems and control, which are covered under the cs.SY sub-category.
